A thread in Java at any point of time exists in any one of the following states.
A thread lies only in one of the shown states at any instant:

1.New State
2.Runnable State
3.Blocked State
4.Waiting State
5.Timed Waiting State
6.Terminated State

1. New -> Instance of thread created which is not yet started by invoking start()

2. Runnable -> After invocation of start() & before it is selected to be the run by the scheduler

3. Running -> After thread scheduler has selected it.

4. Non-Runnable -> Thread alive, not eligible to run

5. Terminated -> run() method has exited